thought:
**Navigating the Administrative Unit Shift**

Okay, so I'm presented with the task of figuring out the new administrative location for "Xã Xuân Thượng, Huyện Xuân Trường, Tỉnh Nam Định". First things first, I need to understand the big picture. We're dealing with a province merger, so the first step is always to check the relevant resolutions. Resolution 60-NQ/TW is clear: "Tỉnh Nam Định" is now part of "Tỉnh Ninh Bình."

Now that I have the new province name, my focus shifts to the "Other resolutions" and "New wards" list, looking for any changes impacting "Xã Xuân Thượng." I methodically go through each of the provided resolutions, but the initial ones don't seem promising. They mention "xã Xuân Trường" and "xã Xuân Thượng", but in provinces that are not relevant to my query. I keep an eye out for mentions of "Xã Xuân Thượng" or "Huyện Xuân Trường".

Finally, resolution 1674/NQ-UBTVQH15 catches my attention. It's focused on "Tỉnh Ninh Bình," the new province, so this is where I expect to find the information I need. It outlines the restructuring of wards in "Tỉnh Ninh Bình", but it doesn't describe the fate of "Xã Xuân Thượng". It outlines the merger of "thị trấn Xuân Trường" and other "xã" into the new "xã Xuân Trường". It's unfortunate that my initial search didn't provide a direct answer. It seems I need to consult other sources to find the new administrative unit for "Xã Xuân Thượng, Huyện Xuân Trường, Tỉnh Nam Định".
